10. Conclusion

The proposed invention introduces an AI-assisted predictive hardware health monitoring framework for modular medical devices capable of detecting progressive subsystem degradation before visible operational failure occurs.

By combining embedded subsystem monitoring, rule-based evaluation, AI-assisted anomaly detection, health scoring, and preventive maintenance recommendation capabilities, the invention improves device reliability, serviceability, and operational uptime while maintaining separation from therapy delivery and patient-critical functionality.
